Two quick notes before you paste them in:

First, I used the reusable template `pipelines/build-dotnet-framework-webapi.yml@templates` because its parameters match what your current combined build is already doing: restore solution, build project, publish to folder, zip, then publish artifact.  

Second, the template’s publish step currently keys off `buildProject`, not `publishProject`, so setting both is harmless, but technically `publishProject` is not being used by the template today. 

The next file to change after you create these two is your SIT release YAML, because it must stop expecting one shared application build and start accepting one build number for MVC and one build number for API.
